# Vyasa Intelligence - Project Rules

## Technology Stack & Local Environment
### Development Environment Setup
- **Developer**: Solo Developer
- **Machine**: MacBook Pro M1, 32GB RAM, Sequoia OS
- **Containerization**: Docker with Colima/Rancher Desktop
- **OS**: macOS Sequoia

### Port Management
- Never use port 5000 for any application
- Use npx serve for static HTML/CSS/JS applications
- API runs on port 8000
- Gradio UI runs on port 7860
- Redis on port 6379
- Ollama on port 11434

### Default Technology Stack
- **Backend**: Python 3.11+ with FastAPI
- **Frontend**: Gradio for demos, React for web apps
- **Database**: ChromaDB (vector), Redis (cache)
- **LLM**: Ollama (local) → Groq (production)
- **Embeddings**: BAAI/bge-base-en-v1.5 (local)
- **Testing**: pytest + Ragas evaluation
- **CI/CD**: GitHub Actions with 4-gate pipeline

## Project-Specific Rules

### RAG System Architecture
- **Corpus**: Mahabharata (~200,000 verses, ~4-5M tokens)
- **Chunking**: Mahabharata-aware hierarchical chunking by Parva/Adhyaya
- **Retrieval**: Hybrid (BM25 + dense) with Reciprocal Rank Fusion
- **Reranking**: BGE cross-encoder or ColBERT
- **Generation**: LLM with strict citation format [Parva, Section]

### Code Standards
- **Python**: Follow PEP 8, use Black for formatting
- **Type Hints**: Required for all functions
- **Documentation**: Docstrings for all modules and classes
- **Error Handling**: Proper exception handling with logging
- **Environment**: Use .env for secrets, never commit

### Development Workflow
- **Branch Strategy**: main (production) ← develop ← feature/*
- **Commits**: Conventional commits (feat:, fix:, docs:, etc.)
- **Quality Gates**: 
  - Unit/integration tests must pass
  - Ragas evaluation: faithfulness ≥ 0.85, answer relevancy ≥ 0.80
  - Security scan: no HIGH severity issues
- **Deployment**: Local → Docker → K8s → Cloud (AWS/Azure)

### Data Management
- **Raw Data**: Store in data/raw/ (never commit large files)
- **Processed Data**: Store in data/processed/
- **Vector Index**: ChromaDB in data/chroma/
- **BM25 Index**: Pickle file in data/bm25_index.pkl
- **Golden Dataset**: data/processed/golden_dataset.jsonl

### Security & Privacy
- **PII Redaction**: Use Presidio for PII detection/anonymization
- **API Keys**: Store in environment variables or AWS Secrets Manager
- **Guardrails**: Implement content safety (AWS Bedrock/Azure Content Safety)
- **RBAC**: Role-based access control for document access

### Performance Requirements
- **API Latency**: P50 < 1s, P95 < 3s, P99 < 5s
- **Retrieval Time**: < 200ms for vector search
- **LLM Generation**: < 2s (Groq), < 30s (Ollama CPU)
- **Memory Usage**: Optimize for M1 Mac (32GB RAM)

### Testing Strategy
- **Unit Tests**: tests/unit/ - Test individual components
- **Integration Tests**: tests/integration/ - Test pipeline flows
- **Quality Gates**: tests/integration/test_quality_gates.py
- **Load Tests**: Use Locust or k6 for stress testing
- **Evaluation**: Ragas metrics on golden dataset

### Documentation Requirements
- **README.md**: Project overview and setup instructions
- **CHANGELOG.md**: Track all changes
- **API Docs**: FastAPI auto-docs at /docs
- **Architecture**: Diagrams using Mermaid
- **Deployment**: Terraform/Bicep IaC documentation

### LLM Integration Rules
- **Provider Abstraction**: Use factory pattern for Ollama/Groq/Bedrock
- **Prompt Templates**: Use structured templates with citations
- **Fallback**: Always have local Ollama as fallback
- **Tracing**: Enable LangSmith for observability
- **Cost Management**: Prefer Groq free tier, monitor usage

### Container & Deployment Rules
- **Dockerfile**: Multi-stage builds, minimal base images
- **Docker Compose**: Local development setup
- **Kubernetes**: Use Rancher Desktop for local K8s
- **Resource Limits**: Set CPU/memory limits appropriately
- **Health Checks**: Always include /health endpoint

### Monitoring & Observability
- **Metrics**: CloudWatch/Azure Monitor integration
- **Tracing**: LangSmith for RAG pipeline traces
- **Logging**: Structured logging with appropriate levels
- **Alerts**: Set up for latency, errors, and quality metrics

## Special Instructions for AI Assistant
- When implementing retrieval, always consider the Mahabharata's hierarchical structure
- For entity queries, prioritize BM25 retrieval
- For philosophical questions, use HyDE query expansion
- Always include proper citations in generated answers
- Test evaluation gates before any deployment
- Consider cost implications of LLM choices
- Maintain backward compatibility when switching providers
